result.execSummary:
The defendant Michel Lester Wortman Sr was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Ignition Interlock Device Tampering/Failure to Install [Modifiers: Extend Order for Ignition Interlock Device], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 347.413(1).
  • Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

11:27 a.m. Defendant in court with Atty Jeanne Zamzow. Andrew Christenson for the State of WI.

Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST.

COURT dismisses 16TR844. Finds defendant Guilty on Count 2 and orders $150.00 fine plus court costs, 6 month extension of IID, and DNA. Court finds defendant giluty on Count 3 and orders court costs. Court dismisses but read in Count 1. Defendant has 60 days to pay or payment plan.

Court adjourned at 11:36 a.m.
Plea/sentencing hearing on November 22, 2016 at 11:30 am.

1:52 p.m.  Defendant present in court with Atty Jeanne Zamzow.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Statement by Atty Zamzow - goes over the last hearing and defendant has now set up a payment plan on the monies due.  Statement by the Court.  Statement by the defendant.  Court will set for Plea & Sentencing on November 22, 2016 at 11:30 a.m. 

Court adjourned at 1:53 p.m.
Settlement Form (PTC)
Status hearing on September 27, 2016 at 01:30 pm.

10:09 a.m.  Defendant present in court with Atty Jeanne Zamzow.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Statement by Atty Zamzow - have an agreement, defendant will plea to count 2 and 3 with a fine and costs, and count 1 will be dismissed and read-in.  State concurs.  Atty Zamzow concurs.  Defendant concurs.

Court goes over plea questionnaire with the defendant.  Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights.  Court goes over the elements of each offense.  Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty.  Court instructs defendant regarding deportation.

Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty on counts 2 & 3 as charged.  Court orders count 1 be dismissed and read-in and orders 2016TR844 be dismissed.  Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered here today.  Sentencing statement by DA.  Sentencing statement by Atty Zamzow.  No statement by the defendant.  Statement by the Court - will not accept the agreement due to other outstanding financial obligations and will allow the defendant to withdraw his plea.

Court sets for Status Hearing on September 27, 2016 at 1:30 p.m.

Court adjourned at 10:18 a.m.

Court instructs the defendant of the maximum penalty on each count.  Court finds probable cause.  Atty Roeth enters a plea of NOT GUILTY on behalf of the defendant.  DA makes bond recommendation.  Court sets bond at $500.00 signature bond. Court will set for Status Hearing on August 29, 2016 at 10:00 a.m.
